What is Destructuring?

Destructuring is a shortcut to extract values from arrays or objects into variables.

Array Destructuring
Normal Way ❌
let fruits = ["Apple", "Mango", "Banana"];

let f1 = fruits[0];
let f2 = fruits[1];
let f3 = fruits[2];
Destructuring Way ✅
let fruits = ["Apple", "Mango", "Banana"];

let [f1, f2, f3] = fruits;

console.log(f1);
console.log(f2);
console.log(f3);

Output:

Apple
Mango
Banana
Skipping Values
let numbers = [5, 10, 15];

let [a, , c] = numbers;

console.log(a);
console.log(c);

Output:

5
15
Object Destructuring
Normal Way ❌
let student = {
    name: "Atharv",
    age: 19
};

console.log(student.name);
console.log(student.age);
Destructuring Way ✅
let student = {
    name: "Atharv",
    age: 19
};

let { name, age } = student;

console.log(name);
console.log(age);

Output:

Atharv
19
Renaming Variables
let student = {
    name: "Atharv",
    age: 19
};

let { name: studentName, age: studentAge } = student;

console.log(studentName);
console.log(studentAge);
Mini Task
let student = {
    name: "Atharv",
    age: 19,
    city: "Pune"
};

let { name, city } = student;

console.log(name);
console.log(city);

Output:

Atharv
Pune
Key Takeaways
Destructuring helps extract values easily
Arrays use [ ]
Objects use { }
Makes code shorter and cleaner
Very important for React and modern JavaScript
